snippet.textDisplay:
This song is not in Baluchi language but is in Brahvi. This is a Brahvi song. 
I am a fluent native Baluchi speaker and I wrote down the actual lyrics in BALUCHI! 

I saw her and she was dazzling like a China doll.
“Man aeiya dist’ant o aa shnzag’ant bitta chyna doddok’ent pema.”

She cast her net as she circled around me.
“Aiya wati jaar rechient owdikha chakarat mani kerra”

Her eyes shone like embers
“Aiye cham shanzet’ant ishkr’ent pema” 

Anyone who lies eyes on her falls for her
“Harkass aiy’ent sara cham aeir’ka, aa aiye vasta kappi”

And I cannot rest until I embrace her
“O mani goma wapsag nabi danke man aiya bakr’ant” 

Since people already suspect it, why don’t we embrace each other before someone stops us?
“Mardom ani gache cham kashageya, gora ma chiya bakr nakane yak degir’ent goma”

Before this I only had a hunch, but when I got near I became certain
“Sariya mana kali yak mehsus bitta, baleh man nazzik aat’ka mana yakkin aatk”

In the evening I will go search for her
“Begaya/shap’ant man rawa aiya patt’ant”

So I hid under the tree listening
“Gora man chertapet’ant drchk’ent chera eshkanaga”

Her words ringing sweet in my ears, like sugar
“Aiy’ent lbz raa’ant vashe mani gush’ent tooka, shakar’ent pema (shirkin)”

When I drew nearer I saw her talking to someone
“Ka man nazzik shotta man dist’ant aa kassiye goma habar kanaga bitta”

How long has he made me wait when I am desperate to be with him?
“Chicho deir man intezaar kana aiye vasta, k mana aiye goma biyagiy’ent?”

Tears streamed down her eyes
“Ars aiy’ent cham’ant che rechag’ant bittaga”

Tears streamed down her eyes
“Ars aiy’ent cham’ant che rechag’ant bittaga”

Believe me I am incomplete without you
“Yakin ka mana, man naks’ant tai badoun”

Her companions told her not to cry
“Aiy’ent dazgwaar’ant goshta magiwr” 

Let be because the destination is far
“Bihl’ent parcha maksad deer’ent”

If it’s meant to be, then these hearts will be one again
“Agr zndh’ent gora ent del yak beyante pada”

Free Baluchistan!!

What a shame. I am Baluch from Southern Baluchistan (Makran) and I can 100% confirm that this song is NOT in Baluchi and is infact Brahvi. Brahvi and Baluchi are entirely different hence why I don’t understand the song.

If the uploader or company wants to spread something then do it in the right way. 
What is even more shameful are the brainwashed so called ‘Baluch’ people praising this song putting a Pakistani emoji flag alongside their comment. A shame to your true motherland, Baluchistan. Bunch of traitors. Allah shomara sai rast’entya baart’ent
